%N A084755 Let the sequence s_n be defined by s_n(1) = n+1 and for k > 1, s_n(k) = k*s_n(k-1)+1. Then a(n) is the first prime in the sequence s_n.
%C A084755 For n = 10r+1, a(n) >= s_n(6).
%e A084755 a(3) = 113: 3+1 = 4 is composite, 2*4+1 = 9 is composite, 3*9+1 = 28 is composite, 4*28+1 = 113 is prime.
%o A084755 (MATLAB) s = n + 1; k = 2; while (~isprime(s)) s = k*s + 1; k = k + 1; end a = s
